{"TopicId":213124,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal\u0026#039;s lose all momentum when exiting jetpack mode","CreatedByName":"RedderThanMisty","CreatedById":215672,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T11:03:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RedderThanMisty","CreatedById":215672,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T11:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version - 0.1.0.0.20892\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version\u00A0 Windows 10\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU and GPU models, any other system\u00A0information which could be relevant - GTX 1080, Ryzen 5 3600\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug. \u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected Behavior - On the mun, when travelling via jetpack, kerbals should keep their momentum when exiting \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E mode.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObserved Behavior - When exiting jetpack mode, kerbals will stop in mid\u0027air\u0027 and drop to the ground.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to Replicate - Land on mun, get kerbal out, plant flag, start flying long distance with jetpack, exit jetpack mode by hitting r.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MackeFerret","CreatedById":226576,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T14:21:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVersion: \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003E0.1.0.0.20892\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003EOS: Windows 11 Home 64bit (10.0, version 22621)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003ECPU: 12th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-12600KF (16CPUs), ~3.7GHz\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003EGPU: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003EExpected Behaviour\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0 Keep speed when putting away jetpack.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003EObserved Behaviour: Putting away the jetpack removes all speed except for about 9.2-9.3 m/s, if you are going faster than that speed.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003ESteps to replicate:\u00A0 Land on the Mun, go on EVA, activate the jetpack, gain speed and put the jetpack away. If launched and gone on EVA after taking off, bug persists.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(249,249,249);\u0022\u003EWorkaround: Not putting the jetpack away.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vdUM7CE.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/vdUM7CE.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yakvi","CreatedById":178649,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T19:28:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E0.1.0.0.20892w\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EWindows 10 v. \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E21H2\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU and GPU models: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU: i7 6700K, GPU: GeForce GTX 1070\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug. \u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E: Kerbals falling from the orbit should not survive contact with the Mun surface\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObserved Behavior: \u003C/strong\u003EAfter reaching altitude of ~12km ASL, every time an EVA kerbal toggles on \u003Cstrong\u003Eor\u003C/strong\u003E off the jetpack, their velocity is reset to 0.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to Replicate\u003C/strong\u003E: \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nReach the Mun orbit above 12km\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGo to EVA and decelerate using the jetpack\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAfter reaching 12km altitude, toggle the jetpack\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n-\u0026gt; Kerbal\u0027s Velocity reaches 0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWait until Mun\u0027s gravity increases kerbal\u0027s velocity again\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRe-enable the jetpack\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n-\u0026gt; Kerbal\u0027s Velocity reaches 0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUsing this trick you can safely land without ever using the jetpack to decelerate\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFixes / Workarounds (if known..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDon\u0027t use this trick\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA list of ALL mods. \u00A0If the list is long, please consider using a spoiler window.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003ENone, vanilla only.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Notes / Screenshots / Log Files (if possible..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nProbably the case on other planets, didn\u0027t test.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/TDPRjq9\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/TDPRjq9 \u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApologies, this seems like a duplicate of the bug below. Hopefully, additional information (threshold of ~12 km) will be helpful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022226576\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4907594529\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/213178-jetpack-stops-all-speed-when-deactivated/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4244134\u0026amp;embedComment=4244134\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-4244134\u0022 style=\u0022height:264px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T19:00:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBug reports merged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}